---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Diego Cuñado — CV" minimal={true}>
  <main>
    <header>
      <h1>Diego Cuñado</h1>
      <p class="role">Head of Product</p>
      <p class="contact">London, UK · diegocunado@gmail.com · +44 74497 10889</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Profile</h2>
      <p>Head of Product with 8+ years building B2B SaaS and marketplace platforms. I've nearly doubled conversion rates, shipped 0-to-1 products, and designed API-driven systems serving thousands of partners and enterprise clients. I write SQL daily, ship features in TypeScript when needed, and build working prototypes to validate ideas fast.</p>
      <p>Deep hands-on experience with AI/LLM integration: I build and operate AI-powered products daily using Claude and OpenAI APIs, including prompt engineering, RAG architectures, and agentic workflows. I understand LLM trade-offs (hallucinations, latency, cost) because I deal with them in production, not just in theory.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

      <h3>Hire Space — Head of Product <span class="light">Jan 2024 – Present</span></h3>
      <p class="company-desc">Two-sided B2B marketplace connecting 5,000+ venues with corporate event organisers. API-driven platform serving enterprise partners.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Nearly doubled site-generated bookings through conversion optimisation and flow redesign after migrating platform from .NET to Next.js</li>
        <li>Increased managed booking win rate from 15% to 21% by identifying drop-off points and introducing AI-assisted productivity tools</li>
        <li>Own platform architecture decisions: authentication flows, API integrations, payment systems, and partner onboarding</li>
        <li>Rebuilt terms acceptance flow with explicit signing process, reducing booking issues from ~10% to ~1%</li>
        <li>Shipped internal tools used daily by 30+ team members, replacing email/spreadsheet workflows</li>
        <li>Closed SEO gap with main competitor from 30+ points to under 8 through technical improvements</li>
        <li>Work directly with enterprise clients on requirements, integrations, and roadmap prioritisation</li>
        <li>Built functional prototypes to validate product ideas before committing engineering time</li>
        <li>Dual-audience prioritisation: balancing internal team needs against external partner requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Hire Space — Senior Product Manager <span class="light">Feb 2021 – Jan 2024</span></h3>
      <p class="company-desc">Led multiple new product launches from concept to market, each addressing a distinct gap in the platform.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Launched Arena, a virtual events platform filling the gap between Zoom and enterprise solutions (Hopin)</li>
        <li>Increased automatic booking win rate from ~2% to 5% by analysing funnel data and redesigning key touchpoints</li>
        <li>Released Instant Book flow allowing clients to book and pay immediately rather than waiting days in negotiations</li>
        <li>Built MVP corporate portal for centralised event management and reporting</li>
        <li>Managed third-party integrations and partner-facing API requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>JustPark — Product Manager, B2B <span class="light">Oct 2019 – Feb 2021</span></h3>
      <p class="company-desc">Sole PM responsible for building a new B2B product line from scratch, coordinating 20+ developers.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Built Luna, a data portal for multi-site car park operators, from initial concept through launch and iteration</li>
        <li>Adapted platform for public sector, winning tenders including Camden, Dundee, and Northern Ireland</li>
        <li>Launched fleet parking solution opening a new revenue stream serving 700k+ potential drivers</li>
        <li>Released parking insurance product via third-party integration, leading partner coordination and user flow design</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Odicci — Digital Product Manager <span class="light">Oct 2017 – Oct 2019</span></h3>
      <p class="company-desc">First PM hire. Built product roadmap from scratch with no design team or established processes.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prioritised growth features that drove 60% revenue increase</li>
        <li>Ensured GDPR compliance from day one for the data capture platform</li>
        <li>Doubled the number of campaign modules while improving cross-device compatibility</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>AI & Technical Projects</h2>
      <h3>AI Agent Systems <span class="light">2025–present</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Built and operate production AI systems using Claude and OpenAI APIs: autonomous email workflows, content generation, multi-channel communications</li>
        <li>Designed prompt logic, context management, and memory systems using vector databases and semantic search (RAG)</li>
        <li>Hands-on with LLM trade-offs in production: hallucination mitigation, latency optimisation, cost management across different model tiers</li>
        <li>Built agentic workflows orchestrating tool use across APIs, databases, and external services</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Chowdown <span class="light">chowdown.me — live product, 30+ countries</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>AI-powered food tracking with autonomous content generation: vision APIs for food recognition, LLM-driven blog publishing across multiple platforms</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Skills</h2>
      <div class="skills-grid">
        <div>
          <strong>AI/ML</strong>
          <p>LLM APIs (Claude, OpenAI), prompt engineering, RAG, vector databases, agentic workflows, AI feature integration</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Platform & APIs</strong>
          <p>API design, auth systems, payments, partner integrations, SDK adoption patterns</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Data</strong>
          <p>SQL (daily), A/B testing, dashboards, KPIs, funnel analysis</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Development</strong>
          <p>TypeScript/JavaScript, AWS, GCP, Vercel, rapid prototyping</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <p>Bachelor of Economics · Universidad Autónoma de Madrid</p>
      <p>Bachelor of Laws · Universidad Autónoma de Madrid</p>
      <p>Scrum Master Certification · Scrum Alliance</p>
    </section>

    <section class="footer-note">
      <p>Spanish (native), English (fluent) · UK since 2012, London area</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  @media print {
    main { padding: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }
    header { margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important; }
    section { margin-bottom: 0.4rem !important; }
    h2 { margin-top: 0.5rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.2rem !important; font-size: 0.85rem !important; }
    h3 { font-size: 0.8rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.1rem !important; }
    ul { margin: 0.15rem 0 !important; }
    li { font-size: 0.75rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.05rem !important; line-height: 1.3 !important; }
    p { font-size: 0.75rem !important; line-height: 1.3 !important; }
    .skills-grid { gap: 0.3rem !important; }
    @page { margin: 1.2cm; }
  }

  main {
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    background: #fff;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
    padding-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; margin: 0; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .role { font-size: 1rem; color: #444; margin: 0.2rem 0; font-style: italic; }
  .contact { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #666; margin: 0.2rem 0 0 0; }
  section { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 0.95rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 0.2rem; margin-top: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; color: #333; }
  h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.2rem 0; color: #1a1a1a; }
  h3 .light { font-weight: normal; color: #666; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .company-desc { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin: 0 0 0.3rem 0; }
  ul { margin: 0.2rem 0 0.5rem 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  li { font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.15rem; line-height: 1.4; }
  p { font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0.2rem 0; }
  .skills-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .skills-grid strong { font-size: 0.82rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.1rem; }
  .skills-grid p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #444; margin: 0; }
  .footer-note { border-top: 1px solid #ccc; padding-top: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.8rem; }
  .footer-note p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #555; }
</style>
